  <name>Seed</name>
  <summary>A hyper.media protocol client</summary>
  <description>
    <p>
      Seed is a hypermedia protocol client that enables you to create, share, and collaborate on content in a decentralized network.
      Built on peer-to-peer technology, Seed allows you to own your data while staying connected with others.
    </p>
    <p>
      Features include:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>Create and edit rich documents with collaborative editing</li>
      <li>Decentralized peer-to-peer networking</li>
      <li>Own your data with local storage and sync</li>
      <li>Share content securely across the network</li>
      <li>Cross-platform compatibility</li>
    </ul>
  </description>

